{"_id":"EAAuto01","name":"The Ancient","type":"automata-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mechanical-arm.svg","system":{"description":"<p>An Automata of unknown origin, shrouded in mystery. Its exterior is adorned with intricate markings inscribed with a language no one comprehends. Its weapons fire bolts of energy that ripple through the air like waves. Many speculate it is of extraterrestrial origin. It seems to have a will of its own, almost as if alive and sentient.</p>","berserkText":"<p>Your Automata doesn't just berserk, it awakens. Channeling unfathomable energy that once laid dormant within its ancient frame. Your Automata's markings glow with a blinding otherworldly light. You channel a storm of energy that takes up an entire zone for the rest of your Berserk. Targets who begin their turn in this zone suffer Light Damage directly to their Ego Field (cannot be reduced). Targets who hit 0 Ego Field due to this effect combust, dealing Heavy Damage immediately. Humans directly exposed will have their Ego drained until they disintegrate.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":2,"agility":2,"wits":1,"empathy":3},"statArrayB":{"strength":2,"agility":1,"wits":3,"empathy":2}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAuto02","name":"The Beast","type":"automata-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mechanical-arm.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Designed with a secondary mode that adds versatility, allowing it to adapt to a wide range of combat scenarios. The transformation is a cosmetic and operational shift, unlocking new weapons, abilities, and tactics. The engineers sacrificed some functions in exchange for the ability to change forms, embodying the belief that adaptation and flexibility are crucial.</p>","berserkText":"<p>You're losing control to your natural instincts. The same primal senses baked into most predators are now yours. They expected a machine, but you'll give them a monster. You immediately fall into your Automata's Alternate Mode and hunch onto all fours. You may engage enemies up to Medium Range with Melee attacks as you launch your arms outward. Every time you destroy an enemy, raise your Ego by 1 (cannot pass max).</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":2,"agility":3,"wits":2,"empathy":1},"statArrayB":{"strength":2,"agility":1,"wits":3,"empathy":2}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAuto03","name":"The Collateral","type":"automata-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mechanical-arm.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Specifically designed for scorched earth. Unlike other mechs with precision weapons, this one boasts wide-arching armaments capable of leveling entire cities. Rather than relying on pinpoint accuracy, it overwhelms the enemy with sheer force. Deciphering friend from foe is not in its nature.</p>","berserkText":"<p>The most dangerous thing to the world around you isn't the Horrors, it's you. Your damage is increased to the next tier up and you gain the Friendly Fire Flaw Tag on all your attacks. Turn the battlefield into a wasteland and the enemy into a fresh corpse. It doesn't matter if your friends are in your line of fire — bring the pain. Destroy and drop buildings on people, cause property damage, and turn this place into a war zone.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":2,"agility":2,"wits":1,"empathy":3},"statArrayB":{"strength":3,"agility":1,"wits":2,"empathy":2}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAuto04","name":"The Eldritch","type":"automata-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mechanical-arm.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The frame of this Automata has been built upon and grafted with remains of several HORRORs. Many core component parts have been supplemented with bio-mechanical ones, and this Automata features a cockpit that does not protect the pilot from Horror Toxicosis — rather, it invites it in. Many pilots don't last long in the Eldritch, and those that do tend to come back as different people altogether.</p>","berserkText":"<p>This is the worst-case scenario. Your Automata is more Horror than giant war machine, and it's off the leash. The cosmic absolute surges wildly within you, causing your Automata to contort and change. Consume all Horrors and prove you're every bit of the monster they claim you to be. Every time you kill an enemy, you rapidly consume them, absorbing them into your Automata and letting loose a blood-curdling Panic, gaining an additional Slow Action you can take immediately this round. This effect can activate multiple times in a round.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":3,"agility":1,"wits":3,"empathy":1},"statArrayB":{"strength":1,"agility":3,"wits":3,"empathy":1}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAuto05","name":"The Heavy","type":"automata-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mechanical-arm.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A metallic colossus that looms over the battlefield. Its thick armor plating and heavy weaponry were designed to withstand the fiercest of attacks and deal devastating blows in return. The one man army capable of slowly moving a parade of death into the heart of any Horror nest. What was sacrificed in mobility was made up for in creating a fortress-sized tank.</p>","berserkText":"<p>It's time to relish what you do best. Safeties are off and it's dangerous all the time. You pilot a walking tank, so who would dare stand in your way? Pick the biggest enemy in the battle and focus all your hatred on them. If someone would try and take your kill, fire on them too; you don't recognize friendlies. Meanwhile, you deal double base damage to your chosen opponent.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":3,"agility":1,"wits":2,"empathy":2},"statArrayB":{"strength":3,"agility":2,"wits":1,"empathy":2}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAuto06","name":"The Junker","type":"automata-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mechanical-arm.svg","system":{"description":"<p>A classic Automata once formidable on the battlefield, now considered outdated and inefficient. Its armor is visibly worn and rust is creeping in. Even with its obvious shortcomings, this Automata has proven to be a reliable workhorse. Its value lies not in its technology but in its history and the bonds formed between it and its pilots.</p>","berserkText":"<p>Even though this Automata is in its dog days, it still has a few tricks up its sleeve. Your Automata detects a surge of adrenaline as you enter a frenzied state, shrugging attacks off like nothing and continuing to push yourself even if you're literally falling apart. All damage done to you is halved (rounded down to a minimum of 1), and you gain +2 to your Close Combat and Ranged Combat.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":2,"agility":1,"wits":2,"empathy":3},"statArrayB":{"strength":3,"agility":2,"wits":1,"empathy":2}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAuto07","name":"The Legion","type":"automata-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mechanical-arm.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Your Automata's ability to operate as a decentralized unit allows for greater flexibility and agility in battle, attacking from multiple angles and entering smaller spaces that larger Mechs cannot access. Only the most skilled of pilots should attempt to pilot this Automata. What it lacks in overwhelming firepower it makes up for in adaptability — being several places at once.</p>","berserkText":"<p>The layers between your Automata and the Legion Units are starting to erode. You're not sure who is thinking the thoughts in your head — you or them? Your Legion Units start to operate on their own, attacking the closest target regardless of whether they're friend or foe. When Legion Units are destroyed, you lose no Ego, and they explode hitting everyone in a zone for Medium Damage.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":2,"agility":2,"wits":2,"empathy":2},"statArrayB":{"strength":1,"agility":1,"wits":3,"empathy":3}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAuto08","name":"The Mass Produced","type":"automata-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mechanical-arm.svg","system":{"description":"<p>This Automata may not have any fancy bells or whistles, but it gets the job done. Its versatility and durability make it a favorite among military organizations. While other specialized Automata may excel in specific tasks, this mass-produced model is a jack-of-all-trades. With a balanced design, it doesn't have any glaring weaknesses that can be exploited by enemies.</p>","berserkText":"<p>They think this Automata isn't special — time to show them how wrong they are. Your Automata pushes into overdrive, you need to find the nearest enemy and face it down one on one. If someone tries to interrupt you, put them out of commission too. Every time you damage the enemy, you can spend a Stunt to target an additional enemy in the same zone. When you destroy an enemy, you demoralize every enemy in that zone with a -1 Penalty to their rolls till the end of the scene.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":2,"agility":3,"wits":1,"empathy":2},"statArrayB":{"strength":1,"agility":2,"wits":3,"empathy":2}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAuto09","name":"The Overload","type":"automata-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mechanical-arm.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The nuclear power source at the heart of the Automata provides immense power and speed beyond what was thought possible. But with great power comes great consequences — the engine's instability poses a constant threat to the surrounding area. Designers added precautions to keep the power draw down, allowing it to push to true power in small bursts. Excessive use causes the engine to overheat and surrounding metal to warp and melt.</p>","berserkText":"<p>Sometimes you just need to let go. You don't need to be warned of pushing yourself too far. You can control it; you only need 1 minute to annihilate your enemies. If that doesn't work, there's always an explosion. Your Automata's Heat is set to 5 and stays at 5 for the duration of Berserk. Every time you destroy an enemy, they melt before your eyes, exploding as if under the effects of Heat End. If the battle ends before your Automata explodes, your Heat is reset back to 0.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":3,"agility":2,"wits":1,"empathy":2},"statArrayB":{"strength":2,"agility":3,"wits":2,"empathy":1}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAuto10","name":"The Prototype","type":"automata-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mechanical-arm.svg","system":{"description":"<p>This Automata is equipped with cutting-edge technology, albeit still experimental. While other Automata aim for more power, this one aims to push the boundaries of what an Automata can do. Possessing features and capabilities not found in other units. There are certain imperfections still in the guise of unforeseen errors and glitches — in the heat of battle, a malfunction could be catastrophic.</p>","berserkText":"<p>Your Automata is the next generation, perfection incarnate. There is nothing that can stand against your advanced weapon of war. It's time to play with your food. Destroy all your enemies in grace, and when an enemy falls in your presence, you must spend a Slow Action consuming the remnants. Your talents don't cost Ego or invoke their normal drawbacks. When you consume an enemy in battle, gain an additional +2 modification to all rolls for the rest of the combat. If there are fallen ally Automatas, consume them too.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":1,"agility":2,"wits":2,"empathy":3},"statArrayB":{"strength":2,"agility":3,"wits":2,"empathy":1}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAuto11","name":"The Stealth","type":"automata-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mechanical-arm.svg","system":{"description":"<p>These units were equipped with abilities to cloak themselves from detection, creating a silent killer. Using the power of the Anathema, this Automata can slip into liminal space between realities. The Stealth is a master of stealth and deception, a hunter of hunters in the darkness. Its enemies fear it above all else, for they begin to feel like prey.</p>","berserkText":"<p>You pushed yourself and your Automata too far, and now your mind is coming apart at the seams. The stealth drive is out of control, and your Automata is switching between this reality and the next. Your Automata only wants to rage, cutting into the nearest thing. You lose control of Unseen Predator as you shift into it at the beginning of your turn, and out of it at the end. You do not lose Ego using Unseen Predator. You gain the ability to move up to two zones in a single Fast Action, and all your attacks from invisibility gain an additional +2 to their die pool.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":1,"agility":3,"wits":2,"empathy":2},"statArrayB":{"strength":2,"agility":2,"wits":3,"empathy":1}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAuto12","name":"The Strainer","type":"automata-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mechanical-arm.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The creators of this Automata made a bold decision to forego the standard stress and neural regulators typically included in most mechs. This allows for greater synchronization between machine and pilot, enhancing overall performance. However, every second spent piloting puts an incredible amount of strain on the pilot's mental and physical well-being. A monument to the little care we show for our pilots.</p>","berserkText":"<p>The beads of sweat, the feeling of your head pounding. You can't control your Automata anymore — it controls you. Your Automata gives you a prime directive, follow it. You gain a level of Stress every turn up to a max of 10. Every time you Panic, you release a powerful psychic blast instead of rolling. When your prime directive is complete, you drop from Berserk.</p><p><em>Psychic Blast: Wits + Command/Manipulation (Higher Skill), Heavy Damage, Area, Knockback, Friendly Fire</em></p>","statArrayA":{"strength":2,"agility":2,"wits":2,"empathy":2},"statArrayB":{"strength":2,"agility":2,"wits":3,"empathy":1}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAAuto13","name":"The Operations Admin","type":"automata-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mechanical-arm.svg","system":{"description":"<p>As the Operations Admin, your role is crucial to the success of any mission. While the pilots may be on the front lines, it is your responsibility to provide them with the information they need to take down the HORRORs. You are also responsible for maintaining Automata, monitoring systems and making necessary repairs. While you may not be physically piloting the Automata, your role is vital to the team's success.</p>","berserkText":"<p>The Operations Admin does not Berserk.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":2,"agility":2,"wits":3,"empathy":1},"statArrayB":{"strength":2,"agility":1,"wits":3,"empathy":2}},"flags":{}}
